@prefix narr: <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Vision> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Vision> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Vision> ;
    narr:childCount "10"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "195e02dff0429a48302c125aa6764e685cb8d15e" ;
    narr:narration """Scarlet's Vision holds the [steering-vector thesis](narr:Narrative_SteeringVector) as its conceptual spine — language, narrative, and meaning act as steering vectors for generative systems, the way velocity steers particle systems — and builds outward from there. The product framing is the [worldview engine](narr:Obs_WorldviewEngine): SMS is merely one thing it can do. The fullest articulation (May–July 2026): [vetting is the beachhead](narr:Narrative_CollaborativeConfigurableAIVision), but the real product is collaboratively configurable AI individuals deployed in pursuit of goals, trustable through citation and visible reference, applicable to every AI task on every vendor. The category word is 'individual' — the antonym of monoculture. The product metaphor is [AI as ship, human at the tiller](narr:Obs_AIAsShip). Two infrastructure ambitions recur: aswritten as [the first thing you install](narr:Obs_FirstThingYouInstall) (like git/GitHub) and a [marketplace of reusable worldviews](narr:Obs_MarketplaceOfWorldviews) — not just skills, but entirety of process and methodology. The July 2026 fundraising reframe sharpens the moonshot: [how many voices are in superintelligence](narr:Narrative_HowManyVoicesInSuperintelligence), not whether AGI arrives. The wedge is enterprise and regulated industries; the ambition is venture-scale on calm-company economics.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_CollaborativeConfigurableAIVision> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_HowManyVoicesInSuperintelligence> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_SteeringVector> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_AIAsShip> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_FirstThingYouInstall> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_MarketplaceOfWorldviews> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_WorldviewEngine> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_SteeringVectorThesis> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_KungFu> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_SharedMemoryQuote> ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "collaboratively configurable AI individuals deployed in pursuit of goals, trustable through citation and visible reference, applicable to every AI task on every vendor" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_CollaborativeConfigurableAIVision> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "the question is how many voices in superintelligence" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_HowManyVoicesInSuperintelligence> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "build diversity of voice on top of the monoculture" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_HowManyVoicesInSuperintelligence> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "This is going to be the first thing that people install when they start a new company. Like you would never consider starting a software company without GitHub and git" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_FirstThingYouInstall> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "A skill is limited context and a set of instructions about how to do something. We're talking about worldview — an entirety of process and methodology and code" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_MarketplaceOfWorldviews> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Language, narrative, and meaning operate as steering vectors analogous to velocity/acceleration in particle systems." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_SteeringVector> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Imagine if [the agents] had shared memory or topics and you could say, Scarlet's bot, Tony's bot, a collaborator's bot — we're all friends. Here's shared memory." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_SharedMemoryQuote> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The July 2026 pitch reframes the moonshot away from 'AI for every task' toward a diversity-of-voice argument — 'how many voices in superintelligence' — which is a different claim than the worldview-engine or individual-companion framings that precede it; the three coexist without explicit reconciliation." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_HowManyVoicesInSuperintelligence> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_WorldviewEngine> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_CollaborativeConfigurableAIVision> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The B2C moonshot ('a companion that evolves with you, that you own, share, fork') is explicitly gated on cost and marked as future-state, sitting in tension with the enterprise/regulated-industry wedge that is the near-term go-to-market." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_CollaborativeConfigurableAIVision> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The shared-memory multi-agent vision ('Scarlet's bot, Tony's bot — we're all friends') points toward a collaborative-network product shape not fully integrated with the individual-AI-companion or worldview-marketplace framings." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_SharedMemoryQuote> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_MarketplaceOfWorldviews> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The steering-vector thesis is framed as foundational to the entire career arc, but its connection to the concrete product (worldview engine, marketplace, individual AI) is asserted rather than argued — a potential gap a skeptic would press." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_SteeringVector> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_SteeringVectorThesis> ] ;
    narr:writer "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6" .
}